The paper deals with a problem of efficient sequential matching of supply and demand in online to offline services, which involves learning to guide individuals to be in the "right" place at the "right" time in the presence of other similar "learning" individuals. The paper proposes an Anonymous MARL (AyMARL) model and employs the principle of maximum entropy to provide a general framework of independent learning that is both empirically effective and theoretically justified. The paper also provides significant improvements in revenue and fairness over existing approaches. Based on these characteristics, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories are cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems), cs.SY (Systems and Control), and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
